One very important thing to note about that, is that if players dont get to absorb levels 1-50 the normal way (not talking PLing alts here. talking pure 1st timers only) they will not learn the numerous critical subtlties of the game.<br>
I just read of a level 59 ranger who didnt know that stationary mobs you get 2x bonus to damage with bow post 50. /shudder. that just scares me.<br>
You can tell which players had huge crutches given to them in their younger years. Its a very subtle thing, but when you group with these ppl in the high level you CAN tell. From the way they disreguard position of their during combat, to not jelling correctly with the differing classes during the combat. etc.<br>
Yes sometimes its just very very poor players who did level up the good old way, but most of the time it is only a player that never learned all the critical aspects of the game that you can only learn from 1-50.<br>
/shrug<br>
